[1]The RAIS S. 58 or Savoia-Marchetti S. M. 58 was an Italian prototype floatplane fighter of the 1920s, designed and manufactured by RAIS.
[2]S. 58En 1924, the Regia Marina (Italian Royal Navy) issued a tender for the replacement of its seaplane fighter Macchi M. 7ter.
Diagonal:2, Size:2
[4]It was a seaplane, a biplane single-seater, built of wood, with a hull based on that of the seaplane race RAIS S. 51, who had participated in the Trophy Schneider 1922.
[5]The engine of the S. 58, a V8 Hispano-Suiza HS 42 produced 296 hp, it was mounted on struts above the hull and it had the effect of a pusher propeller.
